=== 2.6 Logarithm and Exponential

The natural logarithm stem:[\ln x] is the inverse of stem:[e^x]:

stem:[e^{\ln x} = x \quad \text{and} \quad \ln(e^x) = x]

Key identities:

- stem:[\ln(ab) = \ln a + \ln b]
- stem:[\ln(a^n) = n \ln a]
- stem:[\ln(1) = 0], stem:[\ln(e) = 1]

In GPT, the cross-entropy loss uses stem:[\ln p] where stem:[p] is a probability (Chapter 11).
Because stem:[p \in (0, 1\]], stem:[\ln p \leq 0] — the log-loss is always non-negative.

